Jan 3 2006	I love Arizona Charlie!!	The only thing I found wrong with this hotel was the distance to the Strip. I stayed here with a friends family, the grandma had booked all the rooms so we had no choice. I later found out the rooms were 29 dollars a night, you can't beat that! I stayed in one of their suites, it had been recently remodeled. It was spotless, spacious, and comfortable. Breakfast everyday in the Sourdough Cafe, everything tasted fine. The casino served it's purpose. The bartender was friendly as well as the cocktail waitresses. I didn't play on any of the tables but that's only because I'm cheap. It cost about 20 dollars to get a cab ride to or from the strip, the only drawback. All in all I would recommend it to anyone!!!	
Sep 20 2005	Better than I expected	My husband, daughter and I stayed at Arizona Charlie's Boulder Hotel and Casino September 4th, for 1 night. Our flight arrived very late Sunday night and we needed an inexpensive place to stay. I was very skeptical due to the reviews that I have read, but we decided to take a chance. I booked the room on the AC website, $49.00 for a Deluxe Suite King/Double. The hotel is undergoing rennovation on the outside. The room we received was very clean, but in need of an upgrade. The front room had a double bed, TV, and sitting area with a sofa. The bedroom had a King size bed and another TV,which was a bonus. The bathroom was small, clean but did have old fixtures. The hotel is more like a motel setting, the rooms could not be reached through the casino, all on the outside as best as I could tell. Check in was very quick but, the lady at the front desk did advise us to make sure we checked out by 11:00 AM. The beds were comfortable and there was not alot of noise. I was concened that there would be alot of noisy people and car doors slamming with the rooms facing the outside. Check out was easy and since we prepaid there was not a hassle. We were pleasatly surprised and got a good deal for the money.	
Sep 1 2005	Perfectly nice motel	I just returned from a 1-night stay at AZ Charlie's Boulder. I was a little worried after reading some postings for this, but I had a nice experience. I arrived before check-in -- around 11:30 am -- but the clerk was nice enough to find me a clean room -- and by the pool, which I requested. The room was basic - 2 beds, bathroom with noisy fan, vanity/sink area, TV, table &amp; chairs. Plenty of hangers in the closet area too. The property's kind of like an apartment complex -- lots of units and a pool area in the middle. I spent about an hour by the pool and, besides being open to guests only, I saw a bike security man ride by at least 3 times. Makes you feel safe. I ate at the breakfast buffet -- no complaints for $4.60. I got my fruit, coffee, juice, eggs and oatmeal. They even have an omelet station. And let's not forget, Charlie's is CHEAP. I would stay there again. It's very convenient to be able to check in and out very quickly, unlike the huge hotels with long lines.	
